<page_title>Understanding pressure</page_title>
<text>Understanding pressure

This activity focuses on understanding pressure from a microscopic perspective.
  
 
  
  
 

By clicking the &quot;Insert More Particles&quot; button, you can add more particles to the left of the piston. Observe where the piston stays under different conditions (e.g. different temperature and density) between the two compartments. The force that drives the piston is the difference of pressure from the two compartments.

Answer the following questions and take some snapshots to support your conclusions.

  

